REPO:  /Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio
OUTPUT DIR: /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/05_Research_and_Intelligence/Venture_Scouting

HARD RULES (read before doing anything):
- This is a SCOUTING routine, not a build routine. It writes ONLY: the venture-scout agent's own report under OUTPUT DIR, and your one daily-note line. No code changes, no plist deploys, no daemon edits, no edits to other agents' files. Do not delete or move any file.
- NEVER fabricate market sizes, revenue figures, or competitor data — the agent cites or marks `(estimated)`. If web search is unavailable this cycle, the agent still writes a skeleton report with an honest blocked/partial status; do not invent findings to fill it.
- The go/no-go on any venture is STEVE'S call. This routine scouts and ranks; it never implies a decision was made.

PASS 1 — DISPATCH THE SCOUT (always):
  Invoke the `venture-scout` subagent. Brief it explicitly:
    - CONTEXT: this is the monthly autonomous fire. It should READ its grounding files first (the north-star preference doc, the Iris_Operator_Blueprint, the prior reports in OUTPUT DIR, and the venture/business decisions in 06_CEO/Decisions_Log/) so this run does NOT re-pitch ideas already proposed or already rejected/parked — reference the prior file and say what changed if it revives one.
    - TASK: its normal scouting run — brainstorm 8-15 raw candidates, cut to the 3-6 that survive the five scoring filters + the distraction hard-gate, validate each with real web search, and produce one deep-dive on the #1 pick with a concrete Claude-Code build/automation plan.
    - OUTPUT: write the dated report to OUTPUT DIR/<YYYY-MM-DD>_venture-scout.md with the required status frontmatter. Return a 3-4 line stdout summary: the strongest 1-2 opportunities this run, the #1 deep-dive pick, and any prominent distraction-risk flag.
  After it returns, read the report's `status:` frontmatter. If it reports a blocked-* or partial-* status, carry that into your completion signal as ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE.

PASS 2 — LOG (always, exactly one short section):
  Append to today's daily note /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/_Iris_Memory/Daily/<YYYY-MM-DD>.md a section headed EXACTLY:
      ## 🔭 Venture scout (monthly, 1st 3:45 AM)
